0-M1 and scala-reflect at 2.13.18. I'm curious if the deterministic setup can support variables since it requires specific coordinates. Also, scala-reflect might only be necessary if macros are involved.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating macro dependencies**\\n\\nI'm exploring the dependencies needed for the test code that uses macros. It looks like scala-reflect is essential for compiling macro expansions. I’m trying to determine if the scala-compiler's testImplementation includes scala.reflect transitively. Also, the deterministic setup from the POM should have scala-reflect included since it's specified as an extra Maven dependency. Now I need to research artifact dependencies and possibly refer to the POM. I'll check the documentation for normal usage too.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Looking into Scala artifact details**\\n\\nI’m considering that the library is related to a Scala artifact. It seems like generated tests would typically involve the Scala plugin along with the scala-library and compiler components. It’s interesting to think about how these elements all work together to facilitate the testing process in a Scala environment. I'm curious about the specifics of how the Scala artifact is structured and its implications for testing.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Maven dependencies**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how the setup allowed for Maven dependencies, but I see that the existing build includes both scala-compiler and scala-library. The artifact POM depends on scala-library, and while scala-compiler isn’t a normal library dependency, it's used to compile Scala tests. It seems like the Forge scaffold for Scala might include extra Maven dependencies due to the library. I need to check if scala-compiler should be added or if it’s already standard for the Scala test scaffold. Also, I’ll look into the Maven POM for version 1.3.0.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_MSkJ6Iq756iFTyfOL5N1NeFq|fc_0ff913a7694a63b7016a42dcf855fc8197a24c524c6a9f31ec", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request, re\nfor v in ['1.3.0','2.0.0-M1']:\n print('---',v)\n data=urllib.request.urlopen(f'https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/apache/pekko/pekko-parsing_2.13/{v}/pekko-parsing_2.13-{v}.pom',timeout=20).read().decode()\n for dep in re.findall(r'<dependency>(.*?)</dependency>', data, re.S):\n  print(' '.join(re.findall(r'<(groupId|artifactId|version|scope)>(.*?)</\\1>', dep)))\nPY", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1313, "output": 1307, "cacheRead": 22528, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 25148, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782766818766, "responseId": "resp_0ff913a7694a63b7016a42dce341f08197970c70f338238a23"}}
